      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GIDEON MONELLI (4) was quickly into stride and burnt early from the middle draw where he gave a sight, finishing second (29.59) and beaten 2.5 lengths over 520m at Cannington. Didn't win last time but still ran one of the quickest times on the card. Deserves serious consideration. ZIPPING COLUMBUS (1) is an honest type who is lining up for his first start here. Scored from box three last time winning by a neck at Sandown (29.49). One of the leading chances again. TARAWI (2) was out of the placings last time but shapes well for this on his dominant win the start prior, getting around Cannington over 520m in 29.83. Smart winner two back and looks a key chance on that form. JUST A FOREMAN (8) cannot be underestimated.",
